Preliminary Investigations: 

Define research questions and hypotheses.
conduct a literature review to identify gaps in existing knowledge.
Develop initial observational and computational methodologies.

Data Collection and Analysis:

Execute observational campaigns using selected telescopes.
Implement data processing algorithms for initial analysis.
Begin collaboration with experts for interdisciplinary insights.

Synthesis and Interpretation:

Integrate observational and computational results.
Validate findings through peer review and collaborative discussions.
Develop theoretical frameworks to explain observed phenomena.
